{"title":"Cross-Modal Interactive Perception Network with Mamba for Lung Tumor Segmentation in PET-CT Images","domain":"CV","seeds":[{"problem":"Progress in PET-CT lung tumor segmentation is hampered by the lack of a large-scale, publicly available dataset with reliable pixel-level annotations, limiting model robustness and fair benchmarking.","method":"Release the PCLT20K dataset: 21,930 2D PET-CT slice pairs from 605 patients, annotated via a rigorous three-stage clinician pipeline to ensure quality and consistency. Data are split 8:2 at the patient level and preprocessed with CT HU clipping to [-1200, -200], PET conversion to SUV and scaling to [0, 255], and resizing to 512×512 to align coordinate spaces. The dataset underpins a comprehensive benchmark across diverse segmentation baselines."},{"problem":"Mamba-based multi-modal segmentation networks tend to overlook cross-modal channel dependencies, making it difficult to learn shared representations and suppress modality-specific noise in PET-CT fusion.","method":"Introduce the Channel-wise Rectification Module (CRM). At each encoder stage, CRM concatenates PET and CT features along channels, treats spatially flattened pixels as channel sequences, and applies a 1D selective state space (Mamba) block to model channel correlations across modalities. A linear + sigmoid projection produces per-channel weights, split per modality, which scale the original PET/CT features to emphasize correlated channels and filter modality-specific noise before fusion."},{"problem":"Standard VMamba’s 2D selective scan struggles to capture complementary regional information between PET (lesion localization, high contrast) and CT (structural detail, high resolution), limiting effective cross-modal fusion for accurate tumor delineation.","method":"Propose the Dynamic Cross-Modality Interaction Module (DCIM). A convolutional stem yields PET regional tokens and partitions CT features into regional patches with fine-grained local tokens. A region Mamba block processes PET tokens to encode global positional cues, while a local Mamba block models dependencies among CT local tokens. PET regional tokens are then added to each CT local token within the same region to guide CT with PET position cues, enabling dynamic, region-to-local fusion. Integrated at multiple stages within a fully SSM-based encoder-decoder (with CVSS blocks for decoding), DCIM delivers state-of-the-art performance on PCLT20K and the public STS dataset."}]}
